    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 32,
        "summary": "David says, Blessed is the man unto whom the Lord imputes not iniquity\u2014David acknowledges his sin\u2014He recommends that the righteous be glad in the Lord and rejoice.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Blessed is he whose transgression is forgiven, whose sin is covered.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Ps. 32:1 Blessed are they whose transgressions are forgiven, and who have no sins to be covered. Rom. 4:7 (7\u20138).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin; Transgress.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Remission of Sins.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Blessed is the man unto whom the Lord imputeth not iniquity, and in whose spirit there is no guile.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guile; Sincere.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When I kept silence, my bones waxed old through my roaring all the day long.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For day and night thy hand was heavy upon me: my moisture is turned into the drought of summer. Selah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0strength dried up as.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I acknowledged my sin unto thee, and mine iniquity have I not hid. I said, I will confess my transgressions unto the Lord; and thou forgavest the iniquity of my sin. Selah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Confession.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Transgress.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 107
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forgive.",
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 141
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For this shall every one that is godly pray unto thee in a time when thou mayest be found: surely in the floods of great waters they shall not come nigh unto him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godliness.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou art my hiding place; thou shalt preserve me from trouble; thou shalt compass me about with songs of deliverance. Selah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 91:1; 119:114.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I will instruct thee and teach thee in the way which thou shalt go: I will guide thee with mine eye.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Teaching.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Be ye not as the horse, or as the mule, which have no understanding: whose mouth must be held in with bit and bridle, lest they come near unto thee.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Many sorrows shall be to the wicked: but he that trusteth in the Lord, mercy shall compass him about.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 13:21; Rom. 2:9; Alma 41:10; D&C 1:3. TG\u00a0Despair.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trust in God.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Be glad in the Lord, and rejoice, ye righteous: and shout for joy, all ye that are upright in heart.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}